-- Sberbank says Russia risks zero growth if capital ouflows continue 
-- By Oksana Kobzeva
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 10:02AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, March 24 (Reuters) - The CEO of Russia's largest bank Sberbank <SBER.MM> said on Monday that the country is at risk of recession and if capital outflows increase to $100 billion, growth will likely hit zero.

